rows.prompt:
This Python code is supposed to count word frequencies but crashes. Identify the bug and provide the corrected implementation:

def word_counts(text):
    counts = {}
    for word in text.split():
        counts[word] += 1
    return counts

rows.answer:
The bug in the code is that it does not handle punctuation marks attached to words. When the code tries to increment the count of a word, it will not be able to find the word in the dictionary if it has a punctuation mark attached.

```python
import re

def word_counts(text):
    counts = {}
    for word in re.findall(r'\b\w+\b', text.lower()):
        counts[word] = counts.get(word, 0) + 1
    return counts
```

```javascript
function debounce(wait, fn) {
  let timer = null;
  return function() {
    const context = this;
    const args = arguments;
    return new Promise(resolve => {
      clearTimeout(timer);
      timer = setTimeout(() => {
        fn.apply(context, args);
        resolve();
      }, wait);
    });
  };
}
